HEADWORD: Cottised
<hw>Cot"tised</hw> <pr>(-t?st)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Set between two cottises, -- said of a bend; or between two
barrulets, -- said of a bar or fess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

